# PySpark_Assignment

This repository contains structured solutions to PySpark assignments designed to build strong fundamentals in Data Engineering and distributed data processing.

Each assignment follows a clean modular structure:

- `util.py` → Core logic (no input/output, reusable functions)
- `driver.py` → Handles input/output and execution
- `test/` → Pytest test cases for validation

---

## Core PySpark Concepts Used

- DataFrame creation (list, RDD, JSON)
- Transformations vs Actions
- Filtering and aggregations
- Joins (inner, left, right)
- Column operations (`withColumn`, renaming)
- Partitioning (`repartition`, `coalesce`)
- UDF (User Defined Functions)
- JSON processing (`explode`, `posexplode`, `explode_outer`)
- Date functions (`to_date`, `current_date`, `datediff`)
- Writing data (CSV, Parquet, Tables)
